"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The seaborn documentation states that the rc argument in set_style() function should only override parameters that are part of the style definition. However, 'grid.color' and 'grid.linewidth' are not part of the style definition. They should be overridden using the higher-level set_theme() function or matplotlib's rcParams.\",\n  \"patch\": \"8c8\\n< sns.set_context(rc=scale_dict)\\n---\\n> plt.rcParams.update(scale_dict)\\n\\n14c14\\n< sns.set_style(rc=style_dict)\\n---\\n> sns.set_style()\\n> plt.rcParams.update(style_dict)\"\n}"